                    <div class='commenttext'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span style="font-size: 120%;">#7 <a href='http://tarotsolutions.blogspot.com/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Anya</a></span></strong> @ 8:36 am August 19th, 2008</span><br />
<p>Trent, I&#8217;ve heard that it&#8217;s actually NOT a good idea to wash chicken or turkey before cooking. Rinsing the bird just spreads any bacteria on its skin all over your kitchen, whereas if you just cook it (without rinsing), the cooking temperature itself kills any bacteria.</p>
