                    <div class='commenttext'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span style="font-size: 120%;">#79 KM Hosfelt</span></strong> @ 8:13 am August 20th, 2008</span><br />
<p>One other tip when buying whole birds. Go for the heavy birds.  Since the skeleton is basically the same same and weigh compared to the total weight of the bird, you will get more meat to bone ratio from a heaveier bird.  Ergo more savings.</p>
